2. What is AI-Driven IaC and why should you care ? :
---------------------------------------------------
    Traditional IAC :                                      AI-Driven IAC  
  manual code writing from scratch                  AI-Assisted code generation
  Consistent documentaion look up                     Context-aware suggetions 
  trial and error debugging                           Automated troubleshooting
  time intensive development process                Rapid prototyping & Iteration 
                                               Natural languages to infrastructre code

In this section, we will understand what AI-Driven Infrastructure as Code means and why it is important for us as DevOps engineers.
We will first look at the traditional way of writing Infrastructure as Code, where we manually write Terraform from scratch. 
In this approach, we spend a lot of time referring to documentation, fixing syntax errors, and using trial-and-error to debug issues. 
While this method works, it is slow and time-consuming, especially when we are learning or experimenting.

Next, we will see how AI-Driven IaC changes this process. Instead of writing everything manually, we use AI to assist us in generating Terraform code. 
AI understands the context of what we are building and provides smart suggestions while we write code. This reduces the need to constantly search documentation and helps us avoid common mistakes.
We will also see how AI helps with troubleshooting, where it can explain errors and suggest fixes, making debugging faster and easier. 
Because of this, we can quickly try different ideas, make changes, and improve our infrastructure without spending too much time on syntax issues.
Another important concept we will learn is how natural language can be converted into infrastructure code. 
This means we can describe our infrastructure requirements in simple English, and AI will generate the corresponding Terraform code for us. 
This makes Infrastructure as Code easier to learn and faster to implement.
Overall, this section helps us understand how AI makes Infrastructure as Code more efficient, more accessible, and more practical for real-world use.

 > The Power of AI in Infrastructure (Simple Explanation) :
 ----------------------------------------------------------
   Before AI :
   -----------
   Before AI, building infrastructure took a lot of manual effort. We spent many hours writing boilerplate code, even for simple resources. Small syntax mistakes or configuration errors were very common and caused repeated failures. 
   We also had to manually apply best practices by reading documentation and examples. Because of this, the learning curve was slow, especially when learning new tools or cloud services.
   With AI :
   ---------
   With AI, the experience changes completely. We can generate infrastructure code in minutes instead of hours. AI helps with instant syntax correction, so errors are caught early. 
   It also applies best practices automatically, based on common standards and patterns. As a result, learning new tools and technologies becomes much faster, and teams can adopt new platforms more easily.

3. How Do We Write Code with AI? :
-----------------------------------
   In the previous section, we understood why AI-driven code generation is important.
   Now, let’s focus on the how part — how do we actually start writing code with AI?
   The simple answer is: vibe coding.

  > What is Vibe Coding? : [ simply Vibe coding means writing code by describing what we want and letting AI generate and refine the implementation]
  ------------------------
     Instead of following the traditional, very detailed, and manual way of coding, we use a concept called vibe coding. Vibe coding means we do not start by writing code line by line. 
     Instead, we start by describing what we want to build and allow AI to help us generate the code.
     In vibe coding, we treat coding as a conversation rather than a strict step-by-step process. We explain our requirement in natural language, and the AI responds by generating infrastructure code. 
     We then review the output, refine our request if needed, and continue the conversation until the solution looks correct.
     This approach allows us to let go of the need to remember exact syntax or every Terraform resource in advance. We still understand what the infrastructure is doing, but we do not worry about writing every line manually. 
     The AI handles the boilerplate and repetitive parts of the code.
 
  > Traditional Approach vs Vibe Coding :
  ---------------------------------------
    Traditional approach :
    ----------------------
    In the traditional approach, writing infrastructure code usually starts with research. We read cloud documentation, study Terraform providers, understand available resources, and then manually write code for components like VPCs, subnets, security groups, and EC2 instances. 
    This requires deep knowledge upfront and involves a lot of trial and error.

    Vibe Coding :
    ------------- 
    With vibe coding, we start from the end goal, not the documentation. We describe the infrastructure we want, such as networking, compute, and security requirements, and AI generates the initial Terraform code. 
    From there, we iterate and improve the code by giving additional instructions or corrections.
    This makes the process faster and more beginner-friendly, while still allowing experienced engineers to move quickly.
  
   > Key Idea Behind Vibe Coding :
   -------------------------------
      The core idea of vibe coding is:
          Focus on intent, not syntax
          Use natural language, not just code
          Iterate quickly with AI assistance
          Understand the output instead of memorizing everything
          Vibe coding does not mean we ignore the code completely. 
      We still review and understand it, but we rely on AI to handle the heavy lifting.
